%h3
  Product
%p
  Products are the biggie. Review and Aggregated Reviews are typically tied to products, so lets start here.
%p
  Products can have descriptive properties as well as <code>offerDetails</code>. 
  Inside the <code>offerDetails</code> is an <code>Offer</code> or an <code>Offer-aggregate</code> which contain things like price, amount or currency.

%p
  The <a href="https://support.google.com/webmasters/answer/146750?hl=en&ref_topic=1088474">google documentation</a> is a little obtuse though. 
  It states that <code>OfferDetails</code> "Includes a nested <code>Offer</code> or <code>Offer-aggregate</code>". 
  Then it states that <code>Offer</code> has a property of <code>itemOffered</code> which "includes a nested Product".

%p
  So is the product nested in the offer? or is the offer nested in the product?
  The answer is: whichever works for you. Google will accept one or the other. So if you have a Product with a nested Offer, the offer will be tied to that product
  and you don't have to include the offerItems property. 
  If you have an Offer with a nested Product, you specify the products with the OffeItems property.

%p
  a few more things to note about products:
  %ul
    %li
      products should be for purchase directly on the page.
    %li 
      product markup should be used on pages with one main product, not a product listing or category page. 
    %li
      Adult-related products are not supported.
    %li
      If the product has been reviewed by a single reviewer, the reviewer’s name needs to be a valid name for a Person (e.g: John Smith).
%p
  Currency is in <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_4217">ISO-4217</a>
  USD will show a $ sign, everything else will show the abbreviated currency format, even countries that use the $ symbol, like Canda & Australia. 
  If the price is formatted like $100.00, google will assume USD. 
  If you use the $ sign in the price and include a different currency, google will use
  the dollar sign in the price, but it will put an abbreviated currency before it. 
  If you format the currency as 100 CAD for example, google will identify the currency code accordingly.    
